    • Field Detail

      • UNDEFINED_TIME

        @Deprecated
public static final double UNDEFINED_TIME
        Deprecated. 
        Never change this to NaN, as a compare of any valid time to this should result to "greater" for some algorithms to work still we found the name "UNDEFINED" more suitable than TIME_MIN_VALUE
        Note: do not interpret the "UNDEFINED" as "time does not matter", as this has implications for, example, routing. If start time is given as UNDEFINED_TIME then LeastCostPathCalculator.Path.travelTime will return Double.NaN, even though the TravelTime.getLinkTravelTime(org.matsim.api.core.v01.network.Link, double, org.matsim.api.core.v01.population.Person, org.matsim.vehicles.Vehicle) is independent of the start time.
        See Also:

      • parseTime

        public static final double parseTime(String time)
        Parses the given string for a textual representation for time and returns the time value in seconds past midnight. It is the same as parseTime(String, char) with the separator set to ':'.
        Parameters:
        time - the string describing a time to parse.
        Returns:
        the parsed time as seconds after midnight.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - when the string cannot be interpreted as a valid time.

      • parseTime

        public static final double parseTime(String time,
                                     char separator)
        Parses the given string for a textual representation for time and returns the time value in seconds past midnight. The following formats are recognized: HH:mm:ss, HH:mm, ssss.
        Parameters:
        time - the string describing a time to parse.
        separator - the character used between hours and minutes, and minutes and seconds.
        Returns:
        the parsed time as seconds after midnight.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - when the string cannot be interpreted as a valid time.
